{"key":"processedPost-11135981","value":{"id":11135981,"first":11134650,"last":11226008,"when":1254059187,"utime":"09/27/09 04:46 PM","content":"I don't use a rack between jars.&nbsp; I stagger them and stack them up, sometimes five or six high.&nbsp; When you move to substrate bags, you should put spacers between them to allow the steam to penetrate all the way around each bag.&nbsp; This is because the bags are much larger than jars and they tend to stick together, making it hard for the heat to penetrate to the middle of the substrate.<br />RR","title":"Re: Question about sterilizing several PF style jars","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}